            "type": "text",
            "text": "A notebook is a controlled environment. A shop floor is not. The same defect-detection model that hit 99% on a clean test set will hit 88% the first time it sees the actual lighting at 6am on a Monday. That gap — the eleven points the slide deck didn’t mention — is where production ML lives."
          }
        ]
      },
